vex /vɛks/

(vexing,vexed,vexes) 

1. V-T If someone or something vexes you, they make you feel annoyed, puzzled, and frustrated. 使烦恼; 使迷惑; 使沮丧 

例： It vexed me to think of others gossiping behind my back. 想到别人在我背后说闲话让我很恼火。 

2. vexed ADJ 烦恼的 

例： Exporters, farmers and industrialists alike are vexed and blame the government. 出口商、农场主和工业家们同样恼火，都谴责政府。 

3.  →  see also vexed

